    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-03-29T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-03-29T15:00:00-05:00" n="685"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d685">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/772a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PDC1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Poole</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-03-29T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 29, 1919, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>563. Two companies railways engineers totalling 720 officers and men proceeding
                    Murmansk. First company left England March 17th. Second company will leave about
                    March 31. Latter company will be accompanied by <persName corresp="#p_RBGWP1"
                        >Brigadier General Wilds P. Richardson</persName> who has instructions to
                    take command of all American troops in North Russia.</p>
                <p>Withdrawal of American troops has not been passed on formally by Supreme War
                    Council. The President however has approved withdrawal when spring conditions
                    permit and his views have been communicated to British, French and Italian
                    Governments. Will advise you if definite plan of withdrawal is perfected.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
